div.p:
AND now that we ſhould be reckoned amongſt a People whoſe Principle is to Fight,—and avenge themſelves;

which aſtoniſhes all them which know it. I believe your own Conſciences tell you that we are harmleſs, and would do you no harm,—but wiſh your Good, &c. It's known that thoſe you have numbred us amongſt, never denyed the bearing of 
                     Sword, nor Outward Weapons;
                   but whoſe Principle is to avenge themſelves.
